{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_68451c33-4c36-4364-aaf2-8650b5945684","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" let me understand the current state. iter1 already added:\n1. A completeness-review pass in agent_loop.py (one-shot, enforced)\n2. The system prompt already has strong completeness guidance\n\nThe iter1 results: train mean 0.8283 → 0.8401, a modest improvement. Some tasks regressed.\n\nKey observations:\n- environmental-esg/identify-issues-in-phase-one-environmental-site-assessment: max 0.15 — STUCK. This is the lowest-scoring task by far (0.09 → 0.15). It barely moved despite the completeness review.\n- employment-labor: 0.6538 → 0.6346 — regressed (the draft-markup-of-settlement-agreement dropped 0.65→0.63, and this is a low area).\n- Several regressions in iter1.\n\nLet me look at the stuck environmental-esg task and a couple of the regressed ones to find the dominant fixable mode. Let me look at the worst stuck task first — environmental-esg at 0.15 is a huge outlier and would yield the biggest lift if fixable.\n\nLet me look at the tools.py too, and the stuck task.","signature":""}],"model":"accounts/fireworks/models/glm-5p2","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2243dbd6-f247-49ae-9765-e42e664078a9","uuid":"d45cd692-3068-48a4-84fc-8465b723cee1"}
