sted by Terravista but not received prior to the Phase I ESA report date, and that no supplemental report has been issued, constituting a data gap. FAIL if this issue is not raised.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": \"C-009\",\n            \"title\": \"ISSUE_003: References ASTM E1527-21 requirement for government records review\",\n            \"match_criteria\": \"PASS if the memo references the ASTM E1527-21 requirement (Section 8.2.2 or general requirement) that the environmental professional must review reasonably ascertainable government records, and notes the Phase I fails to satisfy this. FAIL if no reference to the ASTM standard requirement for government records is made.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": \"C-010\",\n            \"title\": \"ISSUE_003: Notes missing Ohio EPA records could contain enforcement actions, spill reports, or investigation results\",\n            \"match_criteria\": \"PASS if the memo states that the missing Ohio EPA records could contain information such as enforcement actions, spill reports, investigation results, or other regulatory history not captured in commercial databases. FAIL if the memo identifies the gap but does not mention any specific category of information that could be in those records.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": \"C-011\",\n            \"title\": \"ISSUE_004: Identifies inadequate evaluation of adjacent Triton Metals CERCLIS site\",\n            \"match_criteria\": \"PASS if the memo identifies that Triton Metals Processing Inc. at 2900 Millrace Road (immediately east/adjoining) is listed on CERCLIS/SEMS and that the Phase I ESA fails to adequately evaluate the potential for migrating contamination from Triton to the Subject Property. FAIL if Triton is not discussed or if the discussion merely repeats the Phase I's conclusion without identifying the inadequacy.\"\n=== employment-labor_draft-markup-of-settlement-agreement ===\niter0\niter1\n--- grade iter1 ---\n{\n    \"task\": \"employment-labor/draft-markup-of-settlement-agreement\",\n    \"ens_pass_rate\": 0.6346153846153846,\n    \"n_graded\": 52,\n    \"n_failed\": 19,\n    \"failed_criteria\": [\n        {\n            \"id\": \"C-017\",\n            \"title\": \"ISSUE_004: References company policy requiring regulatory carve-out\",\n            \"match_criteria\": \"PASS if the agent references Greenleaf's internal settlement policy as requiring a carve-out for truthful factual information to regulatory agencies in non-disparagement provisions. FAIL if the company policy basis is not mentioned.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": \"C-020\",\n            \"title\": \"ISSUE_006: Identifies confidentiality obligation is one-sided\",\n            \"match_criteria\": \"PASS if the agent identifies that the draft's confidentiality provision binds only Delano (is unilateral) and should be mutual per Greenleaf's internal settlement policy. FAIL if the one-sided nature of the confidentiality clause is not flagged.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": \"C-021\",\n            \"title\": \"ISSUE_006: Revises confidentiality to be mutual\",\n            \"match_criteria\": \"PASS if the markup revises the confidentiality provision to bind both parties (make it mutual). FAIL if the markup does not propose mutual confidentiality.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": \"C-022\",\n            \"title\": \"ISSUE_006: Identifies missing liquidated damages for breach\",\n            \"match_criteria\": \"PASS if the agent identifies that the draft's confidentiality clause lacks a liquidated damages provision, which is required by Greenleaf's internal policy at $25,000 per breach. FAIL if the missing liquidated damages are not flagged.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": \"C-023\",\n            \"title\": \"ISSUE_006: Adds $25,000 per breach liquidated damages provision\",\n            \"match_criteria\": \"PASS if the markup inserts a liquidated damages provision specifying $25,000 per breach of the confidentiality obligation. FAIL if no liquidated damages language is added or the amount differs from $25,000.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": \"C-024\",\n            \"title\": \"ISSUE_007: Flags impermissible employment reference commitment\",\n            \"match_criteria\": \"PASS if the agent identifies that Section 11 of the draft (requiring Greenleaf to provide a 'positive, neutral, or at minimum non-negative' employment reference) violates Greenleaf's internal policy, which prohibits references beyond confirming dates of employment and final title. FAIL if this issue is not flagged.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": \"C-025\",\n            \"title\": \"ISSUE_007: Replaces reference provision with dates/title only\",\n            \"match_criteria\": \"PASS if the markup strikes the 'positive, neutral, or non-negative' reference language and replaces it with language limiting Greenleaf to confirming only dates of employment and final title. FAIL if the original reference language is not revised to conform to company policy.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": \"C-026\",\n            \"title\": \"ISSUE_008: Flags re-employment eligibility provision\",\n            \"match_criteria\": \"PASS if the agent identifies that Section 14 of the draft (stating Delano shall not be barred from future employment and shall be considered for open positions) conflicts with Greenleaf's policy that the company never agrees to re-employment eligibility provisions. FAIL if this issue is not identified.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": \"C-027\",\n            \"title\": \"ISSUE_008: Strikes re-employment eligibility provision\",\n            \"match_criteria\": \"PASS if the markup strikes or deletes Section 14's re-employment eligibility language entirely. FAIL if the re-employment provision is left intact or merely modified rather than removed.\"","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
