{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"chatcmpl-tool-bea05f4d8ea99087","type":"tool_result","content":"ive relief and all other available legal and equitable remedies.\n\n**Section 11. Employment References**\n\nUpon request from any prospective employer or other third party, Greenleaf agrees to provide a positive, neutral, or at minimum non-negative employment reference for Delano. Such reference shall confirm Delano\\'s dates of employment (June 12, 2017, through March 14, 2025), his final title of Vice President of Supply Chain Operations, and shall include a statement that Delano was a valued member of the Greenleaf team who made significant contributions to the Company\\'s supply chain operations during his tenure. All reference inquiries regarding Delano shall be directed to Leanne Foss, Human Resources Director, or her designee. Greenleaf shall instruct Sandra Wojcik, Tyler Huang, Patricia Engel, Leanne Foss, and all other current employees who may receive reference inquiries concerning Delano to refrain from providing any information beyond the reference described above and shall not, under any circumstances, provide any information suggesting that Delano was terminated for cause, for performance-related reasons, or in connection with any internal complaint or investigation. Greenleaf shall issue written instructions to the foregoing individuals within seven (7) calendar days of the Effective Date implementing the requirements of this Section 11.\n\n**Section 12. Mutual Release by Greenleaf**\n\nGreenleaf, on behalf of itself and each of the Releasees, hereby irrevocably and unconditionally releases, acquits, and forever discharges Delano from any and all claims, demands, actions, causes of action, suits, damages, losses, expenses, and liabilities of every kind and nature, whether known or unknown, suspected or unsuspected, that Greenleaf has, has ever had, or may hereafter have against Delano, arising out of, related to, or in any way connected with Delano\\'s employment with Greenleaf or the termination thereof, from the beginning of time through the Effective Date, except for claims arising from: (i) Delano\\'s fraud, embezzlement, or criminal conduct discovered after the Effective Date; (ii) Delano\\'s breach of any provision of this Agreement; or (iii) any obligation of Delano that survives termination of employment under any prior written agreement between the Parties, to the extent that such obligation is not superseded by this Agreement.\n\n**Section 13. No Admission of Liability**\n\nThis Agreement is a compromise and settlement of disputed claims. Nothing contained in this Agreement, including the payment of the Settlement Payment, shall be construed as an admission of liability, wrongdoing, or violation of any federal, state, or local law, regulation, or ordinance by either Party. Greenleaf specifically denies that it engaged in any unlawful retaliation, age discrimination, or other wrongful or discriminatory conduct toward Delano or any other individual. Delano specifically denies any wrongdoing or misconduct in connection with his employment with Greenleaf. The Parties enter into this Agreement solely for the purpose of avoiding the costs, burdens, and uncertainties of litigation and to achieve a full and final resolution of all disputes between them.\n\n**Section 14. Re-Employment Eligibility**\n\nDelano shall not be barred from future employment with Greenleaf and shall be considered for open positions for which he is qualified, on the same basis as any other external applicant, without prejudice or adverse consideration arising from the circumstances of his separation from employment or the claims asserted in connection with this Agreement. Greenleaf shall not maintain any internal notation, flag, code, or designation in its human resources records, personnel files, applicant tracking systems, or any other employment-related database or record that would indicate Delano is ineligible for rehire or that would otherwise adversely affect Delano\\'s candidacy for future employment with Greenleaf.\n\n**Section 15. Representations and Warranties**\n\n**(a)** Delano represents and warrants that:\n\n> \\(i\\) He has not assigned, transferred, conveyed, or otherwise disposed of any claim, demand, right, or cause of action released herein to any person or entity;\n>\n> \\(ii\\) He has not filed any lawsuit, complaint, charge, or other proceeding against Greenleaf or any of the Releasees with any court, tribunal, or governmental agency, other than the Oregon OSHA complaint referenced in the Recitals above (Complaint No. OR-OSHA-2024-11872), and he agrees not to file any such lawsuit, complaint, charge, or proceeding in the future with respect to any claim released herein, except as may be required by law or to enforce the terms of this Agreement;\n>\n> \\(iii\\) He has the full legal capacity and authority to execute this Agreement and","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2243dbd6-f247-49ae-9765-e42e664078a9","uuid":"65055107-7769-4748-9c57-cb9359650665","timestamp":"2026-06-27T05:23:07.928Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"ive relief and all other available legal and equitable remedies.\n\n**Section 11. Employment References**\n\nUpon request from any prospective employer or other third party, Greenleaf agrees to provide a positive, neutral, or at minimum non-negative employment reference for Delano. Such reference shall confirm Delano\\'s dates of employment (June 12, 2017, through March 14, 2025), his final title of Vice President of Supply Chain Operations, and shall include a statement that Delano was a valued member of the Greenleaf team who made significant contributions to the Company\\'s supply chain operations during his tenure. All reference inquiries regarding Delano shall be directed to Leanne Foss, Human Resources Director, or her designee. Greenleaf shall instruct Sandra Wojcik, Tyler Huang, Patricia Engel, Leanne Foss, and all other current employees who may receive reference inquiries concerning Delano to refrain from providing any information beyond the reference described above and shall not, under any circumstances, provide any information suggesting that Delano was terminated for cause, for performance-related reasons, or in connection with any internal complaint or investigation. Greenleaf shall issue written instructions to the foregoing individuals within seven (7) calendar days of the Effective Date implementing the requirements of this Section 11.\n\n**Section 12. Mutual Release by Greenleaf**\n\nGreenleaf, on behalf of itself and each of the Releasees, hereby irrevocably and unconditionally releases, acquits, and forever discharges Delano from any and all claims, demands, actions, causes of action, suits, damages, losses, expenses, and liabilities of every kind and nature, whether known or unknown, suspected or unsuspected, that Greenleaf has, has ever had, or may hereafter have against Delano, arising out of, related to, or in any way connected with Delano\\'s employment with Greenleaf or the termination thereof, from the beginning of time through the Effective Date, except for claims arising from: (i) Delano\\'s fraud, embezzlement, or criminal conduct discovered after the Effective Date; (ii) Delano\\'s breach of any provision of this Agreement; or (iii) any obligation of Delano that survives termination of employment under any prior written agreement between the Parties, to the extent that such obligation is not superseded by this Agreement.\n\n**Section 13. No Admission of Liability**\n\nThis Agreement is a compromise and settlement of disputed claims. Nothing contained in this Agreement, including the payment of the Settlement Payment, shall be construed as an admission of liability, wrongdoing, or violation of any federal, state, or local law, regulation, or ordinance by either Party. Greenleaf specifically denies that it engaged in any unlawful retaliat