{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_8d9f4890-4723-4715-879d-862cbc81fdc3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"chatcmpl-tool-855687d35473f54a","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"mkdir -p /workspace/scratch; cat > /workspace/scratch/iter2-analysis.md << 'EOF'\n# Iter2 analysis — dominant failure mode\n\n## Evidence\n- iter1 added enforced one-shot COMPLETENESS_REVIEW in agent_loop.py.\n- HELPED coverage tasks: cannabis permit +0.132, paid-leave +0.117, development agreement +0.115, form-S +0.089.\n- HARMED analytical-depth tasks: litigation invoice -0.102, arbitration -0.075, CIM teaser -0.073.\n- WORST/stuck: environmental ESA 0.09->0.15 (53 criteria, 45 still failing). employment-markup 0.65->0.63.\n\n## Root mode (cross-task, method-addressable)\nAgent does COVERAGE (list issues) but under-applies the CONTROLLING AUTHORITY:\n1. Doesn't fully locate/read the controlling standard/policy/authority for the task.\n2. Doesn't CLASSIFY each issue by the authority's own defined categories (REC vs data gap vs ASTM deviation; policy-violation term; etc).\n3. For markup/revision tasks, doesn't DRAFT the conforming revision keyed to the authority's specific requirement (exact $, duration, clause).\n4. Doesn't carry the authority's specific facts (mandatory date Feb 13 2024, $25k LD, 12-mo cap, 409A, etc).\n\n## Evidence specifics\n- employment: deliverable missing liquidated-damages insertion, 12-mo noncompete reduction, re-employment strike, reference rewrite to dates/title, 409A savings clause, IP assignment. Agent summarized policy but didn't draft conforming revisions with the policy's exact terms.\n- environmental: agent wrote about a DIFFERENT property (Dayton vs Toledo) in exec summary; missed ASTM category classifications, the Feb 13 2024 mandatory date, BFPP-defense linkage.\n- arbitration/litigation-invoice: regressed on interaction/analysis/dollar-calc criteria — completeness review burned turns re-reading & fighting pandoc reflow, churn without depth.\n\n## Edit (iter2) — system_prompt.md prose (lowest rung, generic method)\nAdded \"Apply the controlling authority — classify and conform, don't just list\" section:\nidentify authority first + read fully; classify each issue with authority's own categories;\ndraft conforming fix keyed to authority's exact term/amount/duration; carry authority's specific facts verbatim.\nMethod only — no task-specific statutes/numbers.\n\n## Validation\nRunning edited harness on 3 distinct tasks (employment, environmental, litigation-invoice) + proxy_eval.\nEOF\necho written","description":"Save analysis notes"}}],"model":"accounts/fireworks/models/glm-5p2","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2243dbd6-f247-49ae-9765-e42e664078a9","uuid":"6ae2cc31-11c0-4755-9cb9-cb3d540448e0"}
